Most reviewed listing¶

Total number of reviews may not nessarily mean that the listing is the most popular. It may just be that the listing has been on Airbnb for a long time. The reviews per month of each listing may therefore be a more accurate measure of a listing's popularity.

By multiplying average monthly reviews and average listing price we can see which neighborhoods generate the most income.

Tuas is an outlier since it only has one listing at a price of $10000. Southern islands has a very high average listing price of$1893, which would not be ideal for the average tourist.

Hence the top 3 neighborhoods are Museum, Orchard and Rochor.*

*Sungei Kadut is excluded since it has only 5 listings.

Which price range has the highest average number of reviews per month?¶

Which amenities correlate with reviews per month?¶

This is done by calculating the distance between the listing and the closest amenity for each amenity type (e.g. Supermarkets, train stations, malls, hawkers)

Create new columns for minimum distance to amenity¶

In [ ]:
def min_distance(point1, point2):
    return point2.distance(point1).min()

geo_df['min_dist_to_supermarket'] = geo_df.geometry.apply(min_distance, args=(supermarket.geometry,))
geo_df['min_dist_to_train'] = geo_df.geometry.apply(min_distance, args=(train.geometry,))
geo_df['min_dist_to_park'] = geo_df.geometry.apply(min_distance, args=(park.geometry,))
geo_df['min_dist_to_hawker'] = geo_df.geometry.apply(min_distance, args=(hawker.geometry,))
geo_df['min_dist_to_tourism'] = geo_df.geometry.apply(min_distance, args=(tourism.geometry,))

From this statistic, we can see train stations, parks and tourist attractions have p values < 0.05 and thus there is a significant correlation for these amenities i.e. When the distance to the closest train station increases by 1km, reviews per month decreases by 0.1380 points, when the distance to the closest park increases by 1km, reviews per month increases by 0.0883 points and when the distance to the closest tourist attraction increases by 1km, reviews per month decreases by 0.0407 points.

Not surprisingly, distance to train stations is an important factor in determining an Airbnb's popularity. The closer the train station, the higher the number of reviews per month.

Total amenity count does not have any correlation with review per month either.

Therfore, the number of amenities in walking distance (1000 meter) is not a significant factor for determining an Airbnb's popularity. This may be because Singapore is a small country and it has a good public transport system; the distance to a single train station is more important than the number of amenities in walking distance because amenities are easily accesible bya short train ride.

In conclusion¶

The most favourable place for an airbnb listing in Singapore is in the neighborhood of Museum, Orchard or Rochor. It should also be close to a train station. It should be priced around $350-$400 per night.
